\f3\b\fs32 \cf3 DWP Evidence
\f1\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\f3\b\fs32 Overview
\f1\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs32 \cf3 DWP Evidence is responsible for the capture, storage and management of digital content that supports internally and externally facing business operations within the Department.
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\i\fs32 \cf3 Evidence
\f2\i0 \'a0is defined as:
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Digital content which supports assertions made by citizens or their representatives, as part of a customer journey, and for which a quantifiable level of trust is required
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Digital content which we need to retain in compliance with BS 10008 so that it may be used in a legal context, typically as part of Fraud investigations or the Disputes & Appeals processes
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Digital content which supports internal processes, and requires enhanced evidential storage features, such as when material is related to agent safeguarding
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs32 \cf3 Associated with evidential items, we may optionally have one or more\'a0
\f4\i known facts
\f2\i0 , which would be stored as metadata as part of the digital asset. Depending upon the nature of the original evidence, levels of\'a0
\f4\i trust
\f2\i0 \'a0relating to the known facts may also be stored. As an example, a verified digital image of a passport could support\'a0
\f4\i known facts
\f2\i0 \'a0related to both date of birth and nationality, with a high level of trust associated with both. Conversely, an image of a birth certificate could support a known fact around date and place of birth, but would have a much lower level of trust associated with it.
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\f2\fs32 DWP Evidence will in time provide an exemplars service for the visual comparison of presented evidence such as overseas passports. Further into the future, it may provide the capability to use cognitive services to compare and score provided materials against those exemplars to assist DWP agents or make automated judgements.
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\f2\fs32 Stored evidence may comprise both digitised content (for example a digital image of a physically presented passport) and records of digital traces to other trusted evidence stores, for example retained data proving a check against a Home Office service.
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\f2\fs32 These assets may include:
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Images of physical or electronic letters, forms, certificates, etc.
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Audio and video files representing evidence of DWP interactions with citizens
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Text-based interactions, such as SMS, web-chat or social media dialog
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Copies of outbound citizen communications where there may be evidential value in retaining them
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Digitally signed data received from other Government departments or trusted third-parties
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs32 \cf3 DWP Evidence scope includes evidence required for delivery of all DWP policy products and services, mandatory reconsiderations and appeals. It is anticipated however, that evidential case management, specifically specialist support for fraud investigations and subsequent prosecution, may require additional and specialised services outside the scope of DWP Evidence.\'a0
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\f2\fs32 Also note that it is specifically not intended as a general purpose unstructured content repository for usage by other ARA products.
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\f2\fs32 DWP Evidence will:
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Provide an evidence upload facility, accessible to suitably authenticated agents and citizens
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Determine and store metadata relating to evidential items, describing the provenance of each, including the context, time, place and process through which they were obtained
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Support trust markers, highlighting evidential confidence, especially where evidence is suspected or known to be fraudulent. This will include an expiry date for associated evidential trust, for example where assertions were based on a scanned passport, they may expire when the passport expires or degrade over time as defined by rulesets.
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Record the history of evidential items
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Identify the most recently received and/or most trusted instances of evidence related to a citizen
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Provide mechanisms to store evidential assertions from other UK Government functions (e.g. NHS Digital or HMRC)
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Guarantee evidential integrity and satisfy any additional requirements to allow evidence to be admissible in a legal context, by compliance with BS 10008
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Provide evidence life-cycle management capabilities (including a GDPR search and remove facility) to support discovery and data retention rules in-line with DWP policy, with facilities to allow other application products to request extensions to the specified removal date where they have a specific business need to do so
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Employ statistical and machine learning techniques to analyse stored evidence to create trust markers for stored content
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Employ content inspection to generate metadata and perform content routing for unsolicited content
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Generate appropriate events when evidential trust expires, or digital assets are modified or deleted
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Support viewing and management of evidence through the common Citizen / Agent UIs
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs32 \cf3 The product will comply with all relevant data protection and access legislation. Data access will be restricted to authenticated & authorised users and services using the DWP Identity & Trust services.
\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

